<TITLE> Signal 3 puts seaports on alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 15 (bdnews24.com)  The weather office has forecast moderate to heavy rains in parts of the country over next 24 hours from Monday noon. An official of the met office in Dhaka said the chances of the downpour were high because of a huge presence of moving clouds twinned with squally winds. The sea was rough since Monday morning, and the fishing boats have been asked to stay close to the shore, said Abdul Mannan. He said they had already issued local cautionary signal 3 at all seaports. Chances of moderate to heavy rains are huge for Dhaka, Khulna and Barisal divisions over next 24 hours, he said. bdnews24.com's Chittagong Bureau quoted Chittagong weather official Abdur Rahman as saying that light rains had been pouring in many coastal districts including Chittagong since morning. Meanwhile, because of squally weather the Chittagong Port Authorities have suspended operations of small ships (lighterage), said Manjur Parvez, the port's radio control man. The big ships have been asked to stay cautious during movement, he said. The air traffic in Chittagong was normal, according to airport officials. bdnews24.
